    "## Model Overview\n",
    "This interactive simulation models how the **basal ganglia (BG)** select between two competing cortical action-drives (A1 and A2), and how a focused ultrasound (FUS)-style modulation of the BG→Thalamus (via GPi suppression) can transiently alter that process — allowing exploration of both *action-flips* and *global disinhibition* regimes.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Network architecture\n",
    "- **Cortex [A1, A2]**: two competing input signals.\n",
    "- **Basal Ganglia**: computes inhibition via GPi/SNr (two-channel) based on cortical drives.\n",
    "- **Scaled GPi**: a node `gpi_scale(t)` that globally scales the inhibitory output of BG to Thalamus.\n",
    "- **Thalamus**: receives the scaled inhibitory signal and relays the disinhibited (or over-disinhibited) channel to cortex/execution.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Sliders & descriptions\n",
    "- **A1**: Strength of cortical drive for action channel 1.\n",
    "- **A2**: Strength of cortical drive for action channel 2.\n",
    "- **gpi_scale_base**: Baseline scaling of BG→Thalamus inhibition (1.0 = normal; lower values reduce inhibition, increasing disinhibition).\n",
    "- **fus_start**: Time (in seconds) when the suppression window begins.\n",
    "- **fus_dur**: Duration (in seconds) of the suppression window.\n",
    "- **fus_depth**: Fractional additional suppression of GPi during the window (0 = none, 1 = full).\n",
    "- **seed**: Random seed (integer) for reproducibility of network weights and simulation behaviour.\n"
  ]
}
